msgstr "ຄ່າ OTP"

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enrolled.certificate.html:26
msgid ""
"The PKCS12 container contains the public and private key of the\n"
"        certificate. The container will also be available for download in the\n"
"        token details."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enroll.paper.html:1
msgid ""
"The Paper token will let you print a list of OTP values.\n"
"    These OTP values can be used to authenticate. You need to use on value\n"
"    after the other."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enrolled.daypassword.html:32
#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enrolled.hotp.html:32
#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enrolled.totp.html:32
msgid ""
"The QR Code contains the secret key of your token. You need to\n"
"            protect it. <b>If you are in doubt, that someone else saw it, please\n"
"            regenerate the QR Code, when no one else is watching.</b>"
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enroll.question.html:1
msgid ""
"The Questionnaire token will let you define answers to questions.\n"
"    When authenticating with this type of token, you will be asked a random\n"
"    question and then need to provide the previously defined answer."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enroll.radius.html:1
msgid ""
"The RADIUS token forwards the authentication request to another\n"
"    RADIUS server. You can choose if the PIN should be stripped and\n"
"    checked locally."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/config/views/config.token.radius.html:2
msgid ""
"The RADIUS token forwards the authentication request to another RADIUS\n"
"    server."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/config/views/config.token.tiqr.html:9
msgid ""
"The Registration Server is this privacyIDEA server. Note that the\n"
"        privacyIDEA server needs to be accessible from the users smartphone."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/config/views/config.token.remote.html:2
msgid ""
"The Remote token forwards the authentication request to another\n"
"    privacyIDEA server."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/config/views/config.token.sms.html:2
msgid ""
"The SMS Token is an event based token. After the user has tried to\n"
"    authenticate with the OTP PIN, an SMS with an OTP value is sent to the\n"
"    users mobile phone. Then user can authenticate with this OTP value in a\n"
"    second step."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enroll.sms.html:1
msgid "The SMS Token sends an OTP value to the mobile phone of the user."
msgstr "ໂທເຄັນ SMS ສົ່ງຄ່າ OTP ໄປຍັງໂທລະສັບມືຖືຂອງຜູ້ໃຊ້."

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enroll.sshkey.html:1
msgid ""
"The SSH Key Token stores the public SSH Key in the server.\n"
"    This can be used to authenticate to a secure shell."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.getserial.html:95
msgid ""
"The Serial number for the OTP value {{ otp }} is\n"
"    <a ui-sref=\"token.details({tokenSerial:serial})\">{{ serial }}</a>."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enroll.spass.html:1
msgid ""
"The Simple Pass Token does not take additional arguments. You only need to\n"
"    specify an OTP PIN."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enroll.tan.html:1
msgid ""
"The TAN token will let you print a list of OTP values.\n"
"    These OTP values can be used to authenticate. The values can be used in an\n"
"    arbitrary order."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/config/views/config.token.totp.html:2
msgid ""
"The TOTP Token is a time based one time password token.\n"
"    It is described in <a href=\"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6238\">RFC\n"
"    6238</a>."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enroll.totp.html:1
msgid ""
"The TOTP token is a time based token. You can paste a secret key or\n"
"    have the server generate the secret and scan the QR code with a\n"
"    smartphone app like the privacyIDEA Authenticator turning your\n"
"    smartphone into an authentication device. You can also use other\n"
"    authenticator apps like Google Authenticator, Microsoft Authenticator, Authy or FreeOTP. But note, that these\n"
"    might have limitations in the supported hash algorithms or other parameters."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/config/views/config.token.tiqr.html:2
msgid ""
"The TiQR Token is an OCRA based Smartphone Token, that can be used to\n"
"    authenticate by just scanning a QR code."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enroll.tiqr.html:6
msgid ""
"The TiQR token is a Smartphone App token, which allows easy\n"
"    authentication by just scanning a QR Code during the authentication process."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/config/views/config.token.u2f.html:2
msgid ""
"The U2F token is a hardware token, that communicates with the browser.\n"
"    You need to set the correct appId, which in fact is the URL of your\n"
"    privacyIDEA installation."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enroll.u2f.html:1
msgid ""
"The U2F token is a token defined by the Fido Alliance.\n"
"    You can register this token with any webservice and with as many web\n"
"    services you wish to."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/config/views/config.token.u2f.html:10
msgid "The URL of your privacyIDEA installation."
msgstr "URL ຂອງການຕິດຕັ້ງ privacyIDEA ຂອງທ່ານ."

#: privacyidea/static/components/config/views/config.token.tiqr.html:55
msgid "The URL that contains the logo of the service."
msgstr "URL ທີ່ບັນຈຸໂລໂກ້ຂອງບໍລິການ."

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enroll.vasco.html:27
msgid ""
"The VASCO serial is read from the VASCO blob. If you want to use this VASCO serial\n"
"    number within privacyIDEA, activate the checkbox. Otherwise privacyIDEA will create a new\n"
"    unique serial number."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enroll.vasco.html:1
msgid ""
"The VASCO token is a proprietary OTP token. You can paste the VASCO token blob\n"
"    in a hexlified format."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/config/views/config.token.webauthn.html:2
msgid ""
"The WebAuthn token is a hardware token, that communicates with the browser.\n"
"    You may set a trust anchor directory, which is a path to a directory\n"
"    containing certificates to trust for WebAuthn authenticator attestation."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enroll.webauthn.html:1
msgid ""
"The WebAuthn token is a token defined by the W3C and the Fido\n"
"    Alliance. You can register this token with any webservice and with\n"
"    as many web services you wish to."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enroll.yubico.html:1
msgid ""
"The Yubico Cloud mode forwards the authentication request to the\n"
"    YubiCloud. The Yubikey needs to be registered with the YubiCloud."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/config/views/config.token.yubico.html:2
msgid ""
"The Yubico Token is a Yubikey that is registered with the YubiCloud\n"
"    service. The Yubikey emits a 44 character one time password. The first 12\n"
"    characters are a unique ID which is used to bind the device to the user."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/token/views/token.enroll.yubikey.html:1
msgid ""
"The Yubikey Token is an USB device that emits an event based One Time\n"
"    Password. You can initialize the Yubikey using the YubiKey personalization\n"
"    tools.\n"
"\n"
"    The secret hex key and the final OTP length are needed here.\n"
"    For tokens compatible with the Yubico cloud service the OTP length must be\n"
"    44 (12 characters UID and 32 characters OTP).\n"
"    When programming the token for the Yubico cloud service, the Public Identity\n"
"    Length must be 6 bytes, which will give you a UID with 12 characters.\n"
"\n"
"    The current OTP length of a programmed YubiKey can automatically be\n"
"    determined by inserting it in the test field."
msgstr ""

#: privacyidea/static/components/dialogs/views/dialog.welcome.html:77
msgid "The added value of privacyIDEA Enterprise Edition"
msgstr "ມູນຄ່າເພີ່ມຂອງ privacyIDEA Enterprise Edition"

#: privacyidea/static/components/dialogs/views/dialog.welcome.html:87
